.SH NAME
Bitcoin::Crypto::Types \- Bitcoin\-specific data types
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 10
\&        use Bitcoin::Crypto::Types qw(
\&                BIP44Purpose
\&                FormatStr
\&                FormatDesc
\&                ByteStr
\&                ByteStrLen
\&                ScriptType
\&                ScriptDesc
\&                BitcoinScript
\&                BitcoinScriptTree
\&                BitcoinDigest
\&                PSBTMapType
\&                PSBTFieldType
\&                IntMaxBits
\&                SatoshiAmount
\&                DerivationPath
\&                TransactionFlags
\&                BitcoinSecret
\&        );
\&
\&        use Bitcoin::Crypto::Types \-types;
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This module is a Type::Tiny library for types which are either specific for
Bitcoin or are used by Bitcoin::Crypto to implement its routines.
.SH "AVAILABLE TYPES"
.IX Header "AVAILABLE TYPES"
.SS BIP44Purpose
.IX Subsection "BIP44Purpose"
An integer with one of the available purpose numbers for BIP44, like \f(CW44\fR.
.SS FormatStr
.IX Subsection "FormatStr"
A string with one of the available format names, like \f(CW\*(C`hex\*(C'\fR.
.SS FormatDesc
.IX Subsection "FormatDesc"
An array reference with exactly two elements, where the first one is
"FormatStr" and the second one is a string with the data encoded in that
format.
.SS ByteStr
.IX Subsection "ByteStr"
A string where each character is 8 bit. Can be coerced from "FormatDesc".
.SS ByteStrLen
.IX Subsection "ByteStrLen"
Same as "ByteStr", but can be parametrized to have a certain length.
.SS ScriptType
.IX Subsection "ScriptType"
A string with one of the available script type names, like \f(CW\*(C`P2WPKH\*(C'\fR.
.SS ScriptDesc
.IX Subsection "ScriptDesc"
An array reference with exactly two elements, where the first one is
"ScriptType" or a string \f(CW\*(C`address\*(C'\fR, and the second one is defined data
specific for that script type.
.SS BitcoinScript
.IX Subsection "BitcoinScript"
An instance of Bitcoin::Crypto::Script. Can be coerced from "ScriptDesc"
or "ByteStr" (or any of its coercion types).
.SS BitcoinScriptTree
.IX Subsection "BitcoinScriptTree"
An instance of Bitcoin::Crypto::Script::Tree. Can be coerced from a
structure by calling "new" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Script::Tree
implicitly.
.SS BitcoinDigest
.IX Subsection "BitcoinDigest"
An instance of Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::Digest::Result. Can be coerced
from a bytestring (will be used as a preimage).
.SS PSBTMapType
.IX Subsection "PSBTMapType"
A string with one of the available PSBT map type names, like \f(CW\*(C`global\*(C'\fR.
.SS PSBTFieldType
.IX Subsection "PSBTFieldType"
An instance of Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::FieldType. Can be coerced from a
string name of the PSBT field, or from an array reference of two values, where
the first one is "PSBTMapType" and the second one is a positive integer with
field code.
.SS IntMaxBits
.IX Subsection "IntMaxBits"
A non\-negative integer which must be small enough to be representable with the
specified number of bits (parametrizable).
.SS SatoshiAmount
.IX Subsection "SatoshiAmount"
A non\-negative integer, represented as a perl number (on 64 bit) or
Math::BigInt object (on 32 bit). Can be coerced from an integer or from a
string.
.SS DerivationPath
.IX Subsection "DerivationPath"
An instance of Bitcoin::Crypto::DerivationPath. Can be coerced from a string
or a class consuming \f(CW\*(C`Bitcoin::Crypto::Role::WithDerivationPath\*(C'\fR.
.SS TransactionFlags
.IX Subsection "TransactionFlags"
An instance of Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::Flags. Can be coerced from:
.IP \(bu 4
Undef
.Sp
Same as calling "new" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::Flags with no arguments.
.IP \(bu 4
HashRef
.Sp
Same as calling "new" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::Flags with arguments
specified in the hashref.
.SS BitcoinSecret
.IX Subsection "BitcoinSecret"
A secret value \- either instance of Bitcoin::Crypto::Secret or
Crypt::SecretBuffer. May be coerced from anything defined into
Bitcoin::Crypto::Secret.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
Type::Library
